text.section:
Each TVA or commission officer appointed and commissioned pursuant to KRS 61.886 to 61.892 throughout every county in the Commonwealth in which TVA or the commission operates or owns or controls property, including leasehold interests:
Shall have and exercise the powers of sheriffs in making arrests for public offenses committed upon, about, or against such property or on public roads and the rights-of-way passing through or over such property;
Shall have and exercise the powers of sheriffs in making arrests in any situation in which a person is placed in imminent danger of death or serious injury;
Shall have authority to carry weapons for the reasonable purposes of his or her office and in performance of his or her assigned duties;
While in pursuit of a person fleeing after committing an act described in paragraph (a) or (b) of this subsection, may pursue the person and make arrest anywhere in the Commonwealth; and
Shall be subject to all the liabilities of sheriffs.
